value.0: "Are you ready to go, <sir/madam>?"
A young guard peers over the battlements. Torchlight glints off your weapon, causing him to pull back.
"Enemies at the gates! Sound the alarm, they've brought a second wave!"

"They don't look like no orcs or goblins to my eyes, poor as they might be. Sir Dylan, perhaps you shouldn't be so quick to call the attack." You can't see the woman intervening on your behalf but, by her voice, she strikes you as a kindly old lady.
"...Who are you and what are your intentions, then? Speak quickly, before my men rain arrows down upon you!"
"Oh dear, maybe I was wrong. Perhaps you should sound the alarm after all, Sir Dylan."

"Then the gods have answered our prayers, Sir Dylan! Father Dyschall has told us that if the gods saw fit that we should live, they would intervene. And now a hero stands at our gates, requesting entrance."
"Where were the gods when the Banner died? Why did their intervention not come then? Step into the light down there, that I may have a better look at you..."

"Aye, I recognize you now. You were the ones who cut our assailants ranks from the rear and took them by surprise. You fought bravely, stranger, and gave our she-mage, Yenna, time enough to cast her spell."
"Yes, forgive my manners as I am still underslept and over-weary from the battle."
"She has retired to her tower since the battle and refused to speak with most anyone, perhaps in fear that you had fallen beneath her blast. She will be grateful to see you whole, I am sure."
"Is he? My men could not find his corpse among the fallen but if you saw it with your own eyes, then I believe it. Perhaps his troops dragged his body with them as they fled."
"Yes, and accept my apologies as it was I who gave the order. The gate was nearly battered through and had she waited any longer, the keep would have been lost."
"Come, let us celebrate the fact that you still live, stranger. Throw open the gates! It's not an enemy who awaits us but a hero who deserves our thanks! Get moving, men! I will meet you below!"
"Take my arm, Momma Dane, and let me help you down the stairs. Your kind company has been a balm to my jangled nerves this night."
"A hero's welcome to the Keep of Cyan, then, stranger. I think the Hand will be pleased to meet you, and doubly pleased to have your help, I am sure."
"I think she misses the guidance of the Banner, though. Too bad you didn't arrive early enough to keep him from falling to the Masked Man's forces. Now the Hand is in charge all alone."
"A reward? Well, yes, I suppose the Hand will want to reward you. You have certainly proven your worth tonight. It was very exciting to see you in action."
"Excellent. I am sure the Hand will want to reward you for your service! I haven't met such a great hero in years."
"But enough of that. I had better get you to the main gates right away. Let us be quick."
"Of course. Speak to me as soon as you are ready."
"The Banner is the highest ranking officer in the keep. Our Lord was killed many years ago, and the Banner has been ruling here ever since. He was killed by the invaders early in the battle."
"The Hand is the commander of the armies and next in charge after the Banner. But we really should get going. I dare not leave my command of the gates for long."

"That one looks like a friendly half-orc to my poor, old eyes. Sir Dylan, perhaps you shouldn't be so quick to call the attack." You can't see the woman intervening on your behalf but, by her voice, she strikes you as a kindly old lady.
"Am I so hideous to you that you would mistake me for a kobold or an orc? We come to help you!"
"Stand back, fool! We are no goblin-kin. Would you attack those who come to help you?"
"Blast you! Do we look like goblins? We're here to help you!"
"Eek! We are not goblins! Do not hurt us, please! You see, <FirstName>, I told you we should not have come here."
"No not yet."
"My identity is unimportant right now. I am here to assist you."
"Keep pointing those arrows at me, boy, and we'll see what rain goes where!"
"Calm down. I just don't like having weapons pointed at me by allies."
"Just don't threaten me again and we should get along just fine."
"There will be no need for that. I am here to help."
"<FullName> at your service, and I mean you no harm."
"My name is <FirstName> and I've come to help your city."
"The night is cold. Will you let us in or no?"
"And she cast it in the nick of time. Give her my thanks."
"The Masked Man was to die at my hands, not hers."
"Yenna, is it? Then the Masked Man is dead by her blast."
"Yes, she damn near incinerated us, I'll have you know."
"I hope this means I'm going to get a reward."
"I am ready when you are."
"I need to rest first."

Comment.value: PC should be able to rest here now, but should not be allowed to leave

value.0: "What is the Banner and the Hand?"
"We are enemies of the Masked Man. We helped break his battle lines."
